---
description: "Runtime config resolution"
alwaysApply: true
---
Classifier system prompts live in settings.json at router.classifier_prompt. Model identity preambles live in the adapter only.

All model aliases (local/qwen3-8b, remote/deepseek-v4-pro, etc.) come from settings.json models mapping. Application code uses the alias string, never the underlying model name.

The ollama_model_names mapping in settings.json translates LiteLLM aliases to Ollama model names. ModelScheduler uses this mapping exclusively.

Intent labels are a stable contract: general_chat, web_search, deep_research, coding_basic, coding_advanced, bash, pdf_gen, file_ops, vision. Use RouteSource StrEnum, never magic strings.